# Project Context

Short, strict, factual. Not a PRD.

## Project Name

oc-visual-test-runner

## Current Stage

Phase 2 — post-click verification and retry logic. Phase 1.5 hover loop implemented. Phase 1 browser visual runner verified 2026-07-01 on cloud runner.

## Project Purpose

**OpenClaw Skill runtime** for persona-based visual UI testing. User NL request → OpenClaw structured input → CLI runner → visual agent loop → artifacts → OpenClaw user-facing summary. Not only a standalone Python script.

## Phase 1 Supported Targets

- `figma` — Figma prototype URL in browser
- `web` — website URL in browser
- Both use a **shared browser adapter**

## Planned Future Targets

- `android` — future platform adapter (not implemented)
- `windows` — future platform adapter (not implemented)

## Core Architecture Direction

```text
OpenClaw (NL → structured input)
  → scripts/ux_testing.py
  → target config → platform adapter → observation frame
  → VLM action decision → action execution → feedback observation
  → trace/result output → OpenClaw user-facing return
```

Organized around a **universal visual agent loop** behind an OpenClaw Skill layer.

## Phase 1 Output (Implemented Target)

- `ux_result.json`, `action_trace.json`, `ux_test_recording.webm`, `screenshots/`
- **Not yet:** `ux_report.md`, `index.html` (Phase 4), OpenClaw end-to-end delivery (Phase 5)

## Current Non-Goals

- No Android or Windows adapters
- No formal HTML/Markdown reports in Phase 1 (Phase 4)
- No OpenClaw / Feishu end-to-end Skill delivery yet (Phase 5)
- No Figma API grounding or DOM-selector-first automation
- No legacy runner migration
- No automatic retry on Gemini 503 yet (future hardening)

## Cursor Agent Must Not Assume

- Phase 1 E2E verified on cloud runner — local Gemini may require VPN; use `--use-stub` for browser-only local checks
- `ux_report.md` or `index.html` exist — Phase 4
- OpenClaw user-facing return is implemented — Phase 5
- Failed clicks automatically mean UX issues
- Legacy `figma_runner.py` / `web_runner.py` exist in this repo
- Real API keys belong in the repo — use `.env` locally only
